Almost feel guilty giving this game four starts instead of the usual five that games from Five-BN score. Two main issues for me: many bugs, game froze three times, forcing to restart the device and the story felt boring and far fetched. Five-BN games are more expensive than most but I'm used to superior quality which justifies the price. 'The Wanderer' fell short for me, unfortunately. I hope the two newer releases will replicate the awesomeness of earlier Five-BN works.

Lost Lands 4: Wow!!! This game was well worth the money. Multiple collections, different puzzles, story line made sense, great voice overs, wonderful graphics... what more can I say???? I am really loving the Lost Lands series.  I have to thank the Five-BN team for fixing an issue I had during the bonus game. I emailed them, they requested my game logs, fixed the issue for me, returned the files and I was able to complete my game. Their customer service was exceptional. I will remember that for my next game choice.  A BIG THANK YOU TO THE FIVE-BN TEAM!!!

Let me start by saying that this game deserves five stars. With good quality FMVs and voice work, inventive hidden object screens and bright artwork, Lost Lands 4 is a genre top game. But... I rated it four stars! Two issues hold it back from greatness. Overly hard and (sometimes) poorly explained mini-games dishearten and excessive location warping jars as the game ends. A really good and long game by 5-BN Games, but get ready to skip the mini-games!
